()🔹PasswordPolicy kya hai?
👉 PasswordPolicy ek security rule set hota hai jo decide karta hai:-
👉 User ka password:-
kaise banana hai
kitna strong hona chahiye
kab change karna hai
kaise validate hoga

🔥 🔹 Ye karta kya hai?
👉 PasswordPolicy ka main kaam:-
1️⃣ Password complexity enforce karna:-
minimum length
uppercase / lowercase
numbers
special characters

2️⃣ Password expiry control:-
password kab expire hoga
user ko change karna padega

3️⃣ Password history check:-
purana password repeat nahi kar sakta

4️⃣ Validation check:-
password policy ke against hai ya nahi
strong hai ya weak
-------------------------------------------------
🔥 🔹 PasswordPolicy andar kya hota hai?
👉 Iske andar mostly ye properties hoti hain:-
📌 1️⃣ Length rules:-
min length (e.g. 8)
max length

📌 2️⃣ Character rules:-
uppercase required
lowercase required
digits required
special chars required

📌 3️⃣ Expiration rules:-
password valid for 90 days
warning before expiry

📌 4️⃣ History rules:-
last 5 passwords reuse nahi kar sakte

📌 5️⃣ Lockout rules:-
failed attempts ke baad account lock

📌 6️⃣ Custom rules (advanced):-
regex based validation
custom rules (Java rule)
---------------------------------------------------------
🔥 🔹 DB me kya store hota hai?
👉 Yes 👍 PasswordPolicy DB me store hoti hai,
📌 Table:-
👉 spt_password_policy

📌 DB me kya hota hai:-
policy name
length rules
complexity rules
expiration rules
history settings
lockout settings
associated rules (XML/JSON reference)
------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 🔹 Kya evaluation hota hai?
👉 Yes — policy evaluate hoti hai through:-
👉 PolicyEvaluator

👉 Flow:-
User password change karta hai
PolicyEvaluator run hota hai
PasswordPolicy check hoti hai
Result:-
✅ Valid
❌ Invalid
--------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 🔹 Kya DB me password store hota hai?
❌ Plain password NEVER store hota
❌ Only encrypted / hashed form store hota hai
👉 SailPoint security follow karta hai.
---------------------------------------------------------
🔹 PasswordPolicy – Common Methods (Conceptual List)
📌 1️⃣ Getter Methods:-
getName()
getDescription()
getId()
getCreated()
getModified()

📌 2️⃣ Policy Configuration Methods:-
getMinLength()
getMaxLength()
getRequireUpperCase()
getRequireLowerCase()
getRequireNumbers()
getRequireSpecialChars()
getMinCharacterClasses()

📌 3️⃣ Expiration Methods:-
getExpiration()
getWarnBeforeExpiration()
getMaxAge()
getPasswordExpiration()

📌 4️⃣ History / Reuse Methods:-
getHistoryCount()
getPasswordHistoryCount()
👉 Kaam:-
kitne purane passwords store hone chahiye.

📌 5️⃣ Lockout / Attempts Methods:-
getMaxFailedAttempts()
getLockoutDuration()

📌 7️⃣ Rule Reference Methods:-
getPasswordRule()
setPasswordRule(Rule rule)
👉 Custom Java rule attach kar sakte hain

📌 8️⃣ Setter Methods (Admin use):-
setName(String name)
setDescription(String description)
setMinLength(int length)
setMaxLength(int length)
setRequireUpperCase(boolean flag)
setRequireNumbers(boolean flag)

📌 6️⃣ Validation / Rule Methods:-
validatePassword(String password)
isValid(String password)
👉 Ye actual me check karta hai:-
password policy follow ho raha hai ya nahi
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
✅ getName():-
👉 Policy ka naam return karta hai
