--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 2️⃣ isValid(String password):-
👉 Ye simple check hai (boolean return karta hai)

✔ Kya karta hai:-
password policy follow ho raha hai ya nahi
bas true / false return
👉 Internally ye validatePassword() ka simplified version hota hai.
🔹 1️⃣ validatePassword(String password):-
👉 Ye method detailed validation karta hai
✔ Kya-kya check karta hai:-

1️⃣ Minimum length
password >= min length

2️⃣ Maximum length
password <= max length

3️⃣ Uppercase
at least 1 A–Z hona chahiye

4️⃣ Lowercase
at least 1 a–z

5️⃣ Numbers
at least 1 digit

6️⃣ Special characters
! @ # $ % etc

7️⃣ Character classes
required number of different types

8️⃣ Password history
old password repeat nahi hona chahiye

9️⃣ Custom rule
agar koi custom Java rule attached hai

10️⃣ Expiration check
expired password allow nahi karega.

🔥 Example:-
ValidationResult result = policy.validatePassword("Rahul@123");
🔹 Output (Valid):-
Password is valid
🔹 Output (Invalid):-
Password must contain at least 1 uppercase letter
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
import sailpoint.api.SailPointContext;
import sailpoint.api.SailPointContextFactory;
import sailpoint.object.PasswordPolicy;
import sailpoint.object.Identity;

public class PasswordValidationDemo {

    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {

        SailPointContextFactory factory = new SailPointContextFactory();
        SailPointContext context = factory.getContext();

        Identity identity = context.getObjectByName(Identity.class, "rahul");

        PasswordPolicy policy = context.getObjectByName(PasswordPolicy.class, "Default Password Policy");

        String password = "Rahul@123";

        // Validate password
        boolean isValid = policy.isValid(password);

        System.out.println("Is Password Valid: " + isValid);

        context.close();
    }
}
